Constructor Detail

ConcentricCircle

public ConcentricCircle(boolean before,
                        ConcentricCircle x)
Creates a new circle in an existing chain of concentric circles. The diameter will be the average of the sibling circles, or half/double of the one and only sibling.

public double getDiameter()
Gets the actual diameter. The value may be different from the argument passed to a constructor or setDiameter to keep the rings in the chain concentric.

setDiameter

public void setDiameter(double diameter,
                        double minimumDistance)
Sets the diameter for the circle keeping the value between its neighbours. If the neighbours are closer than twice the minimumDistance, the diameter is set to the average diameter of the neighbours, unless the requested diameter lies between its neigbours.
